            "is_correct": false,
            "beats": [
              {
                "type": "dialogue",
                "text": "Let me show you how this works. First, you check if the biggest number fits. That tells you which scales are even possible. A scale that's too small won't work, no matter what. Then, after you know it fits, you check if the numbers end in 0 or 5. That tells you which scale makes the counting easiest. The answer is: Does the biggest number fit? That's always first.",
